    <statement><p>Add or subtract the rational expressions to a single rational expression and then simplify. If applicable, state the restricted domain.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{{\frac{4}{r-2}-\frac{8r}{r^{2}-4}} =}</m> <fillin characters="40" name="AnSwEr0001"/></p>
</statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>-\frac{4}{r+2}, r\ne 2</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <solution><p><m>\displaystyle{\begin{aligned}
   {\frac{4}{r-2}-\frac{8r}{r^{2}-4}} 
      \amp = {\frac{4}{r-2}}-\frac{8 r}{(r - 2)(r + 2)} \\
      \amp = \frac{4\cdot({r+2})}{({r-2})\cdot({r+2})} -\frac{8 r}{(r - 2)(r + 2)} \\
      \amp = \frac{{4\mathopen{}\left(r+2\right)-8r}}{(r - 2)(r + 2)} \\
      \amp = \frac{{4r+8-8r}}{(r - 2)(r + 2)} \\
      \amp = \frac{{-4r+8}}{(r - 2)(r + 2)} \\
      \amp = \frac{{-4\mathopen{}\left(r-2\right)}}{(r - 2)(r + 2)} \\
      \amp = {-\frac{4}{r+2}, r\ne 2}
\end{aligned}
    }</m></p>
<p>Since the factor <m>{r-2}</m> was canceled, the domain condition lost during the simplification is <m>r \ne {2}</m>.</p>
</solution>
